          <msContents>
            <summary>
              <p>2 fol. on parchment; Shelfmark: Is 1405A; Qurʾānic text: Q 2:60-2:65, Q 2:93-2:101; 15 lines per page; Dimensions: 376 x 286mm; Script style: kūfī D; Estimated date of production: 800-1000. </p>
              <p> </p>
              <p>This fragment is part of the Blue Qurʾān, which has been described in detail by Marcus Fraser (cf. <ref target="https://corpuscoranicum.de/de/manuscripts/1458">entry on the sister fragment HC.MS. 03223</ref> in the Qatar National Library). For more information on the fragment, also see the entry <ref target="https://viewer.cbl.ie/viewer/image/Is_1405A/1/">Is 1405A</ref> on the digital library of Chester Beatty.</p>
              <p> </p>
              <p>The catalogue of Qurʾān manuscripts of Chester Beatty Library contains the following information on the shelfmark Is. 1405, now presumably split into 2 fragments (<ref target="https://www.zotero.org/groups/corpuscoranicum_pub/items/itemKey/JXE6ZPW5">Arberry 1967</ref>, p. 4): </p>
              <p>"4. A small fragment containing Sura II. 57-95. Three folios of firm, deep blue vellum, measuring 27.6 x 36.7 cm., 15 lines to the page. The very beautiful script is executed in gold and is unvocalized. Verse-endings are marked with circular ornaments. <hi rend="italic">Alif </hi>is 1.2 cm. high. The binding is modern, dark-green leather. See Martin, pl. 141 ; Arnold-Grohmann, p. 20; Upham Pope III, p. 1944; Munajjed, 5 (2). See Plate 12. (MS. 1405)"</p>
            </summary>
